data.content:
Anh - Anh
aborning
[ə'bɔ:nɪŋ]
■ adverb chiefly N. Amer. while being born or produced.
Origin
1930s: from a- 'in the process of' + US dialect born 'to be born'.

sentences.en: Once again, Dew said to me, “Ning, divorce her, O.K.? Then we live together.”
